TITLE: TypeScript Definition and Usage of testEffect for Async Testing
DESCRIPTION: Definition and example of the testEffect helper function for testing asynchronous effects in Solid.js. It allows testing reactive effects by providing a done callback rather than using polling.
SOURCE: https://github.com/testing-library/testing-library-docs/blob/main/docs/solid-testing-library/api.mdx#2025-04-12_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
testEffect(fn: (done: (result: T) => void) => void, owner?: Owner): Promise<T>

// use it like this:
test("testEffect allows testing an effect asynchronously", () => {
  const [value, setValue] = createSignal(0);
  return testEffect(done => createEffect((run: number = 0) => {
    if (run === 0) {
      expect(value()).toBe(0);
      setValue(1);
    } else if (run === 1) {
      expect(value()).toBe(1);
      done();
    }
    return run + 1;
  }));
});
```

