TITLE: Configuring ICU Support Check for React Intl Tests
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of ICU (International Components for Unicode) support detection and setup for Node 13+ environments. Includes functions to check ICU support and configure number/date formatting.
SOURCE: https://github.com/testing-library/testing-library-docs/blob/main/docs/example-react-intl.mdx#2025-04-12_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const hasFullICU = () => {
  try {
    const january = new Date(9e8)
    const pt = new Intl.DateTimeFormat('pt', {month: 'long'})
    return pt.format(january) === 'janeiro'
  } catch (err) {
    return false
  }
}

export const setupTests = () => {
  if (hasFullICU()) {
    Intl.NumberFormat.format = new Intl.NumberFormat('pt').format
    Intl.DateTimeFormat.format = new Intl.DateTimeFormat('pt').format
  } else {
    global.Intl = IntlPolyfill
  }
}
```

